<span style="color: #00008B;">**SLFP**</span> - *Sri Lanka Freedom Party* - This is us. Founded as a center-left party in 1954, we have switched back and forth from governing, normally in coaltion with other left wing parties and leading the opposition until 1977. We are historically advocates for democratic socialism and promoters of sinhalese nationalism. 

[? if slpp_formed: <span style="color: #E52B50;">**SLPP**</span> - *Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna (Sri Lanka Peoples Front)* - A right wing sinhalese nationalist party. Formed after a recent split from the <span style="color: #00008B;">**SLFP**</span> ?]

[? if slmp_formed: <span style="color: #663399;">**SLMP**</span> - *Sri Lanka Mahajana Pakshaya (Sri Lanka Peoples Party)* - A left wing progressive party. Formed after a recent split from the <span style="color: #00008B;">**SLFP**</span> ?]

<span style="color: #006400;">**UNP**</span> - *United National Party* - A center-right party led by [+ unp_leader +], promoting economic liberalization and open-market policies economically with an emphasis of sinhalese nationalism socially. Formed before independence they have switched back and forth between governing and opposition with us for decades. 

<span style="color: #F7D917;">**TULF**</span> - *Tamil United Liberation Front* - Currently the primary political voice for Tamil nationalism, advocating for Tamil rights and autonomy. Since 1977 they have activly advocated for seperatism from Sri Lanka through peaceful methods. They are currently losing their influence to tamil militant groups who also advocate for independence...through violence. 

[? if pflt_formed: <span style="color: #DC143C;">**PFLT**</span> - *Peoples Front Of Liberation Tigers* - The political front of the <span style="color: #DC143C;">**LTTE**</span>, they advocate for further autonomy for the north-east on a anti caste, revolutionary socialist and esplicity tamil nationalist platform. ?]

<span style="color: #FDCC01;">**ACTC**</span> - *All Ceylon Tamil Congress* - Established in 1944, the ACTC was one of the earliest Tamil political parties, advocating for Tamil rights and federalism. Orginally a member of the <span style="color: #F7D917;">**TULF**</span>, the <span style="color: #FDCC01;">**ACTC**</span> split off in 1978 over internal disagreements. 

[? if eros_formed: <span style="color: #FF2400;">**EROS**</span> - *Eelam Revolutionary Organisation Of Students* - Founded in 1975 in London by Tamil expatriates, <span style="color: #FF2400;">**EROS**</span> began as a Marxist think-tank before evolving into a militant group advocating for Tamil independence. It has recently joined democratic politics under a similar Marxist outlook. ?]

[? if dplf_formed: <span style="color: #CE2029;">**DPLF**</span> - *Democratic Peoples Liberation Front* - Founded as the political front of the <span style="color: #CE2029;">**PLOTE**</span> and other smaller former militant groups. It advocates for Tamil autonomy and harsher measures against the rival <span style="color: #DC143C;">**LTTE**</span>. ?]

<span style="color: #FF2226;">**JVP**</span> - *Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna (Peoples Liberation Front)* - Established in 1965 by Rohana Wijeweera, its is a Marxist-Leninist party known for its failed insurrection in 1971 against the <span style="color: #00008B;">**SLFP**</span> government. It advocates for a rural based revolutionary socialism. In recent years it has started adopting sinhalese nationalist positions. 

[? if npp_formed: <span style="color: #9F005D;">**NPP**</span> - *National Peoples Power* - Founded after a recent split within the <span style="color: #FF2226;">**JVP**</span>. It is a broad left wing coalition that advocates for democratic socialism. It also contains communist, feminist and minority factions. ?]

<span style="color: #65000B;">**CPSL**</span> - *Communist Party Of Sri Lanka* - Established in 1943, the <span style="color: #65000B;">**CPSL**</span> aligned with pro-Soviet Marxist-Leninist ideology, advocating for workers' rights and socialism. We have often being in coalition with them. 

<span style="color: #A91101;">**LSSP**</span> - *Lanka Sama Samaja Party (Lanka Equal Society Party)* - As Sri Lanka's oldest socialist party, founded in 1935, the <span style="color: #A91101;">**LSSP**</span> played a pivotal role in the independence movement and post-independence politics. The party focuses on workers' rights, social justice, and anti-colonialism. Their formidable trade unions have recently been crushed by the <span style="color: #006400;">**UNP**</span>.

<span style="color: #FF8080;">**NSSP**</span> - *Nava Sama Samaja Party (New Equal Society Party)* - Formed in 1977 following a split from the <span style="color: #A91101;">**LSSP**</span>, the <span style="color: #FF8080;">**NSSP**</span> embraces Trotskyist ideology with a focus on self-determination and anti-authoritarianism. It has established itself as a vocal advocate for Tamil rights and democratic socialism.

[? if mep_formed: <span style="color: #FF3915;">**MEP**</span> - *Mahajana Eksath Peramuna* - Originally formed in 1956, it has recently been reactivated, emphasizing Sinhalese nationalism and ethnic chauvism. It is a minor political party. ?]

<span style="color: #E52B50;">**CWC**</span> - *Ceylon Workers Congress* -Representing Indian Tamil plantation workers, they focus on labor rights, social welfare, and political representation for their marginalised base. It has recently grown closer to the <span style="color: #006400;">**UNP**</span> under JR.

[? if ucpf_formed: <span style="color: #E52B50;">**UCPF**</span> - *Up Country Peoples Front* - A newly founded party for Indian Tamils. It represents the part of their community upset with the CWC and its ineffectivness in addressing their needs. ?]

[? if slmc_formed: <span style="color: #2DCF3E;">**SLMC**</span>  - *Sri Lanka Muslim Congress* - Founded recently, the SLMC has emerged to represent the interests of the Muslim minority, particularly in the Eastern Province. The party aims to address grievances of the Muslim community and prevent their youth from joining militant groups. ?]


