= Tamil Militant Groups

**LTTE** - *Liberation Tigers Of Tamil Eelam* - Originally formed in 1972 as the "Tamil new tigers" by its leader Velupillai Prabhakaran, the LTTE is the most infamous of the militants for their uncompromising stance and dedication to their fight for Tamil Eelam through armed struggle. At present they are small by their organisation is unrivaled. The LTTE also draws most of its support from the Karaiyar "fishing" caste.

**EROS** - *Eelam Revolutionary Organisation Of Students* - Established in 1975 by members of the diaspora in London as a marxist "thinktank". It is highly ideoligical with an emphasis on socialism and social justice, unlike the other militants they have made efforts to integrate muslims. EROS also maintains extensive links with the tamil diaspora and other liberation movements such as the PLO. Its armed wing recently split off, weakening them. EROS draws most of its support from educated middle class and urban tamils such as the Vellalar caste.

**EPRLF** - *Eelam Peoples Revolutionary Liberation Front* - Formed in 1980 by breaking away from EROS due to ideological and strategic differences, the EPRLF seeks to blend tamil nationalism with revolutionary socialism and anti-casteism. They are also one of the weaker militants owing to their recent foundation. EPRLF draws support from lower caste tamils disatisfied with the tradtional caste system. Uniquely the EPRLF supports closer connections with and greater rights for the indian tamils in the highlands.

**TELO** - *Tamil Eelam Liberation Organisation* - Founded by Nadarajah Thangathurai in 1979, it was inspired by EROS and the LTTE. It has since become one of the more prominent groups. It draws suppprt from the Karaiyar "fishing" caste like the LTTE. Its loose organisational structure has made it the boon of the police and military. Like EROS it has links with movements like the PLO. Ideologically it is rather muddled outside of support for Tamil Eelam and social justice. 

**PLOTE** - *Peoples Liberation Organisation Of Tamil Eelam* - PLOTE was founded around 1980 by Uma Maheswaran as a split from the LTTE over both personal and strategic conflict between their two leaders. PLOTE draws support from university educated and urban tamils but also from various other castes highlighting its anti-casts stance and socialist ideolgy mixed with tamil nationalism. It is however a small organisation with a small number of dedicated cadre's.

